== 盐度 ==
唐胡安池是一個高盐的池塘。它的溶解固体总量是有记录以来第二高的，盐度約為[[死海|死海]]的1.3倍。池水的盐度會随时间变化，从200到474 g/L，主要由[[氯化钙|氯化钙]]组成。它是南极唯一一个几乎从不结冰的高盐湖。<ref name='astrobio'>[https://www.astrobio.net/mars/salty-antarctic-pond-replica-mars-water/ Salty Antarctic pond could be a replica of Mars' water] {{Wayback|url=https://www.astrobio.net/mars/salty-antarctic-pond-replica-mars-water/ |date=20201109031113 }}. ''Astrobiology Magazine''. 23 November 2017.</ref>唐胡安池塘周围覆盖着氯化钠和氯化钙盐，这些盐是随着水分蒸发而[[沉淀|沉淀]]的。<ref name="#1"/><ref>{{cite book|last1=Oren|first1=Aharon|editor1-last=Whitton|editor1-first=Brian A.|editor2-last=Potts|editor2-first=Malcolm|title=The Ecology of Cyanobacteria: Their Diversity in Time and Space|date=2007|publisher=Springer|isbn=9780306468551|page=287|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qRfoBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA287|accessdate=27 March 2018|chapter=Salts and Brines|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421054018/https://books.google.com/books?id=qRfoBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA287|dead-url=no}}</ref>

唐胡安池的面积和体积随时间而变化。根据美国地质调查局1977年发布的地形图，该地区面积约为{{convert|0.25|km2|acre|abbr=on}}。然而近年来这个池塘已经大大缩小了。1993-1994年的最大深度被描述为“一英尺深”（{{convert|1|ft|cm|disp=output only}}）。1997年1月，它大约有{{convert|10|cm|in}}深；<ref name='astrobio'/>1998年12月，除了几十平方米的面积外，整个池塘几乎都干涸了。大部分剩余的水都流到了池塘周围的洼地里。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mcmlter.org/content/lake-levels|title=Lake Levels|format=csv|publisher=McMurdo Dry Valleys Long-Term Ecological Research|accessdate=28 March 2018|archive-date=2018-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704093450/http://www.mcmlter.org/content/lake-levels|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 生命 ==
目前在唐胡安池的高盐水體中還沒有發現任何生命形式，研究人員曾經在顯微鏡下有看到疑似細菌的東西，但沒有更直接的證據，科學界認為缺乏有機物的高鹽水體難以支持生命的存在。<ref name="NAT-19790830">{{cite journal |last1=Siegel |first1=B.Z. |last2=McMurty |first2=G. |last3=Siegel |first3=S.M. |last4=Chen |first4=J. |last5=Larock |first5=P. |title= Life in the calcium chloride environment of Don Juan Pond, Antarctica |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_nature-uk_1979-08-30_280_5725/page/828 |journal=[[Nature_(journal)|Nature]] |date=30 August 1979 |doi=10.1038/280828a0 |volume=280 |issue=5725 |pages=828–829|bibcode=1979Natur.280..828S }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20150928">{{cite news |last=Chang |first=Kenneth |title=NASA Says Signs of Liquid Water Flowing on Mars |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/29/science/space/mars-life-liquid-water.html |date=28 September 2015 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |accessdate=28 September 2015 |archive-date=2019-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808103911/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/09/29/science/space/mars-life-liquid-water.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NAT-20100425">{{cite journal |last1= Samarkin |first1=Vladimir A. |last2=Madigan |first2= Michael T. |last3=Bowles |first3=Marshall W. |last4=Casciotti |first4=Karen L. |last5=Priscu |first5=John C. |last6=McKay |first6=Christopher P.|last7= Joye |first7=Samantha B. |title= Abiotic nitrous oxide emission from the hypersaline Don Juan Pond in Antarctica|journal=[[Nature|Nature Geoscience]] |date=25 APRIL 2010 |doi=10.1038/NGEO847 |volume=3 |pages=341–344 }}</ref>

